00:08:28.330 --> 00:08:29.340
There's no scattering.

00:08:29.340 --> 00:08:32.840
So this is saying that sigma--

00:08:32.840 --> 00:08:34.679
how should I say it?

00:08:34.679 --> 00:08:41.220
The delta l-- I'll just say
delta l's are small or very

00:08:41.220 --> 00:08:42.929
small--

00:08:42.929 --> 00:08:49.080
small-- for l greater than k a.

00:08:49.080 --> 00:08:53.280
The delta l, the phase
shifts, enter here,

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:55.540
as sine squared of
the phase shifts.

00:08:55.540 --> 00:08:58.680
So they must be very small,
