00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:22.050
you get nothing.

00:09:22.050 --> 00:09:27.830
If k a is much less than 1,
only l equals 0 will contribute.

00:09:27.830 --> 00:09:36.230
If k a is 1 or 2, it's--

00:09:36.230 --> 00:09:39.560
I think I would write here, if--

00:09:39.560 --> 00:09:47.350
we don't have to be very
small, but around 1, very few

00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:48.390
will contribute.

00:09:48.390 --> 00:09:57.970
Or essentially, you could say
that all the l less than k

00:09:57.970 --> 00:09:59.120
contribute.

00:09:59.120 --> 00:10:00.070
They contribute.

00:10:03.910 --> 00:10:10.780
So even if k a, say, was 5, you
could hope that the l's up to 5

00:10:10.780 --> 00:10:12.890
will be a big contribution.

00:10:12.890 --> 00:10:17.320
And after that, they
start to fall off.

00:10:17.320 --> 00:10:18.240
OK.

00:10:18.240 --> 00:10:25.700
So that's one
intuition into the l's.

00:10:25.700 --> 00:10:31.830
Second piece of intuition
comes from the solutions

00:10:31.830 --> 00:10:35.410
